`template/scripts/` is the set of standalone CI/lint gates invoked by `ctx-verify` (or CI directly) to enforce policies from `docs/SPEC.md` that aren't yet real dylint rules, plus one bootstrap script unrelated to verification. Each check script is independently invocable, takes an optional root-path arg defaulting to `.`, and returns a shell exit code (0 pass, 1 fail) with `FAIL: <path>:<line>: ...`-style messages on stderr.

All the enumeration-based checks (`no_allow_check.sh`, `rationale_check.py`, `workspace_lints_check.sh`) deliberately use `git ls-files -z --cached --others --exclude-standard` rather than a filesystem walk, to avoid racing concurrent cargo/rust-analyzer writes into `target/`. This is a shared convention, not an accident — if one script's enumeration strategy changes, check the others for consistency. `cycle_check.sh` and `machete_check.sh` instead shell out to external cargo subcommands (`cargo-modules`, `cargo-machete`) and hard-fail if the binary is missing, rather than skipping — a shared "never silently pass" posture across the whole directory: a missing tool or unparseable output is always FAIL, never a skip, so `ctx-verify`'s aggregate pass/fail stays trustworthy.

`cycle_check.sh` is a placeholder — it confirms `cargo-modules` runs, not that cycles are absent (real work deferred to dylint rule 4). `machete_check.sh` re-parses `cargo machete`'s report with awk into per-dependency FAIL lines. `no_allow_check.sh` bans `#[allow(...)]` outright with zero suppression mechanism. `rationale_check.py` is the most complex: a regex/brace-counting approximation of a Rust parser enforcing function/file length limits with a rationale-comment escape hatch below hard limits. `workspace_lints_check.sh` checks every crate manifest opts into workspace lints via an awk state machine, not a TOML parser.

`install-tools.sh` is unrelated to the checks: it builds and copies `ctx-*` binaries and summarizer prompts from a sibling tooling repo into this project so the other scripts and hooks have their dependencies in place.

No intent.md exists to check divergence against.